metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #7615
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: NAZCA #142
metadata.description:
Real time animation (WebGL)
Variable dimension
2022

Nazca is a group of living glyphs made in the soil of the GPU. There are 17 figures that get combined and mixed over three layers. The figures vary in complexity but are generally created with vertical and horizontal lines only. Figures have at least one seed, some even have a seed per path. A seed is an oscillating pixel that can be compared to a square wave oscillator of audio synthesis and is usually followed by a path or a set of paths. The purpose of the paths is to send the pixels along the lines to make the figures visible through movement and to create a reduction to pure animation.

👽 Kim Asendorf

metadata.name: Microgravity #415
metadata.description:
Microgravity is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Scale symmetry of abstract semiliquid forms.

Click on a section of the image to explore deeper.
- Use keys [0-9] to change the detail level.
- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "R" key to reset the coordinates.

metadata.name: Butterfly Effect #2
metadata.description:
Well known is the butterfly effect, a system where it's not possible to predict how arbitrarily small changes in its initial conditions will affect the outcome.

This piece tries to achieve this with a few simple steps by manipulating uv-coordinates: rotate, distort, repeat n-times. Fitting the notion, the resulting images resemble butterflies. 

Btw, this is my genesis nft project.

To save a hi-res PNG (4096x4096 px), double click or hit 's' (give it a few seconds to generate).

metadata.name: linez #8
metadata.description:
graphical genart with a lot of features that determine the outcome.

the features are selected carefully and allow for rare combinations:
number of bars, palette, animation length, color mode, glitched (very rare), gradient smoothness,
noise elevation and scale, tiling incl. uv mode and "love handles" <3

the scene features full 3D and a simple orbit navigation allows you to discover it. left mouse click to rotate, right click to travel.

i want to thank the following people who built tools that helped me to realize this artwork.
https://p5js.org for an outstanding toolkit
https://twitter.com/liamegan for the FXhash helpers
https://twitter.com/mknol for the super useful random weighted option
https://coolors.co for the palettes
https://twitter.com/shig_nft for reminding us to give proper shout outs 🙌

check out the console =)

metadata.name: Flow Writer #111
metadata.description:
This is a grid-based flow field piece. Variation occurs in colors, size of the flow grid, and the properties of the "streamers" that dynamically draw the piece. The piece will continuously redraw itself after a short delay.

It sometimes feels like a flow field-based piece is a rite of passage in the generative art world. I've explored and used flow fields in a variety of contexts. This piece originally was created while exploring a different concept, for which it did not work. I liked how it sometimes felt organic, sometimes smooth, sometimes jagged, sometimes technical, sometimes painterly... so I decided to spin it off into its own piece. 

Take the piece into full screen and the grid will adjust, using the same noise seed for the flow field, to show a larger composition.

metadata.name: Time #13
metadata.description:
To pass time while in meetings or just trying to solve a problem I like to sketch on my notebook continuous abstract lines, usually following a short pattern without paying too much attention to the process. 

In this project I take this to the extreme in a generative approach. The resulting image is one continuous line imperfectly repeating the same pattern for a minute. You can travel back in time and zoom in to explore all layers.

Instructions:

- use the mouse to navigate (zoom, pan and drag)
- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 't' to switch time travel mode (use your mouse to go back in time)
- press 'p' in 'Open live' to download the current view it in a custom resolution. This usually results in better quality for prints.

Berlin, January 2022
@bgola
